<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 06 at 5:49PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Alamance, Moore,
western Orange, southeastern Montgomery, northeastern Richmond,
eastern Randolph, eastern Guilford, western Lee, northwestern Hoke
and Chatham Counties through 645 PM EDT...
At 548 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near McLeansville to near Siler City to 8 miles
southeast of Biscoe to 12 miles north of Rockingham. Movement was
east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Burlington, Sanford, Graham, Southern Pines, Pittsboro, Carthage,
Siler City, Carrboro, Pinehurst and Mebane.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
